    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/model-ship-security-plan-templates"/>
    <title>Model ship security plan templates</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;These model ship plans will help company and ship security officers to compile a ship security plan (SSP) under the International Ship and Port Facility Security (ISPS) Code, for agreement and verification by the Department for Transport. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The documents are cruise ship and ro-ro (roll-on/roll-off) passenger ferry templates. A &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.dft.gov.uk/mca/mcga07-home/shipsandcargoes/mcga-shipsregsandguidance/mcga_dops_maritimesecurity_mainpage/dops_ms-guidance/mcga_dops_msb_ssp/dops_msb__model_ship_security_plan.htm"&gt;template for use with cargo ships&lt;/a&gt; is available on the &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.dft.gov.uk/mca/"&gt;Maritime and Coastguard website&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
